<Link id="l00029" /><CodeLine lineNumber="29"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// This interface/API is to provide an object oriented way to implement ABI</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00030" /><CodeLine lineNumber="30"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// functionality. This is intended to replace use of the ABI enum to perform</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00031" /><CodeLine lineNumber="31"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// ABI operations. The ABIs (e.g. Switch, Async, Retcon&#123;Once&#125;) are the common</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00032" /><CodeLine lineNumber="32"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// ABIs. However, specific users may need to modify the behavior of these. This</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00033" /><CodeLine lineNumber="33"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// can be accomplished by inheriting one of the common ABIs and overriding one</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00034" /><CodeLine lineNumber="34"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// or more of the methods to create a custom ABI. To use a custom ABI for a</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00035" /><CodeLine lineNumber="35"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// given coroutine the coro.begin.custom.abi intrinsic is used in place of the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00036" /><CodeLine lineNumber="36"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// coro.begin intrinsic. This takes an additional i32 arg that specifies the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00037" /><CodeLine lineNumber="37"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// index of an ABI generator for the custom ABI object in a SmallVector passed</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00038" /><CodeLine lineNumber="38"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// to CoroSplitPass ctor.</span></CodeLine>
